column5: @ 8:00 I decided to go out for a few casts at the river down the hill.  I grabbed my baitcaster from the boat which had an X-Rap on it 8:15 by the time my lure hit the water... fourth cast and BANG!  After a short fight , I took a picture and released it... Walked back to my truck, went to pick up a few coffee @ Hortons and made it back home and posted this in less than an hour..  No tape or scale.. your guess is as good as mine..I'd say about 3lbs   Randy

Gotta love Nipissing but why did you release it??When I used to release pickerel up there, they looked at me like I am crazy or something. Today I understand why. Yum!! It looks a bit over 4lbs.Nice fish.
for me four casts is like the bottomless cup of coffee --- I can always find a reason for 1 more.................. but that is a sweet little wake up .
nice fish and glad to hear it went back. wouldn't be near as tasty and a 1.5lb fish anyways!
Un christy beau doré Randy Félicitation Moi j'y donne 4lbs+ Doesn't get any better then that!!! Thanks for sharing Jacques
Nice Randy. I think that your being modest with the 3 lb. estimate. Congrats on your mini outing. Bet you spent more at Timmies drive through than you did fishing.

Your all business man.  Grab a coffee, walk down to the river, 4 casts in nail a nice Walleye, go home rod slung firmly over shoulder.   Nothing to it.  lol.  You can't beat an evening like that, even if it only took you ten minutes.
Tres beau!  Four casts and a 2.5-3.5lbs walleye? Simply put, you're the man.
The pic is a bit fuzzy, is that a big "mallow" there I see?
I squish it and roll it up to look like an X_rap..
Nice Fish, I think I might have stayed for another cast or two though.  Clarence
Nice walleye Randy. I'm a bit suprised that they are still up or back in the river. Coffee at 9pm?? Do you sleep?
lol i think 2.5 is out of the question.
The Falleye migration is in full swing and will just get better from now 'til closing. The coffee I picked up was for this morning.  Randy
